[The deer hunting season is not yet over so we will continue to see the results of state wildlife surveillance programmes, adding more detail to existing maps of CWD cervid prevalence.

The Science News article is to get you, the reader, thinking. If this initial research on mice is correct and has wider valid implications, CWD infected deer will be less prevalent on acid soils, e.g., east of the Mississippi, and thrive on the alkaline soils on the west side. Therefore it may be possible to be niche modeled and mapped. And this would have the ability of improving the targeting and efficiency of CWD surveillance & control programmes. - Mod.MHJ


